	<p><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Prospective students:</strong> I am recruiting <strong>ONE</strong> Ph.D. student for Fall 2026.<br />
I'll be at the <a href="https://ieeevis.org/year/2025/welcome">2025 IEEE VIS Conference</a> if you would like to chat in person. </span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">We conduct experiments to understand how humans interpret data and make decisions using visualizations, generating guidelines for visualization tools that help people more effectively explore and communicate data to make decisions. Some questions we are interested in answering include...</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">1. How can we design natural language visualization tools to support visual analysis?</span><br />
<span style="font-size: 18px;">2. How are people biased when interpreting data? Why do these biases happen? How can we design information systems that mitigate them?</span><br />
<span style="font-size: 18px;">3. How do we design trustworthy visualizations and analytic tools in the era of AI?</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">Some nice people recorded a talk I recently gave at Stanford University below...</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
